Setting up a python Anaconda environment

1. First install Anaconda

2. Create a virtual environment using the command 
   conda create -n "PIPEnv" python=3.11

Alter the envirnment and python version accordingly

3. conda activate PIPEnv


4. Then run your python code and jupyter notebooks. You will have to install the python modules using conda install <modulename> or pip install <modulename> when it complains
module not found.

5. You can exit the virtual environment using the command

  conda deactivate
